   "source": [
    "# Seaborn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b2e2d4dc-5caf-478c-ba93-a8fb50dfbf7e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Documentation link =>>  https://seaborn.pydata.org/api.html"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b7564838-449f-4530-9f3f-3aa27cc1f0bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Why Seaborn?\n",
    "-provides a layer of abstraction hence simpler to use\n",
    "-better aesthetics\n",
    "-more graphs included"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7cba361f-3f5f-42fd-9d33-6c3b0c79996c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Seaborn Roadmap\n",
    "Types of Functions\n",
    "\n",
    "Figure Level  --->> figure means the container in which the graph contains\n",
    "Axis Level      --->> axis means the axis of a plot or graph \n",
    "Main Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Relational Plot\n",
    "    -relplot\n",
    "    -scatterplot\n",
    "    -lineplot\n",
    "2. Distribution Plot\n",
    "    -displot\n",
    "    -histplot\n",
    "    -kdeplot\n",
    "    -ecdfplot\n",
    "    -rugplot\n",
    "    -distplot\n",
    "3. Categorical Plot\n",
    "    -catplot\n",
    "    -stripplot\n",
    "    -swarmplot\n",
    "    -boxplot\n",
    "    -violinplot\n",
    "    -boxenplot\n",
    "    -pointplot\n",
    "    -barplot\n",
    "    -countplot\n",
    "4. Regression Plot\n",
    "    -lmplot\n",
    "    -regplot\n",
    "    -residplot\n",
    "5. Matrix Plot\n",
    "    -heatmap\n",
    "    -clustermap\n",
    "6. Multiplots grids\n",
    "    Facet grids\n",
    "        -FacetGrid\n",
    "    Pair grids\n",
    "        -pairplot\n",
    "        -pairGrid\n",
    "    Joint grids\n",
    "        -jointplot\n",
    "        -jointGrid\n",
    "    \n",
    "\n",
    "# link of seaborn\n",
    "https://seaborn.pydata.org/api.html"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "deee3959-8ad9-4715-b0fb-651f626eaa61",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To Increase/Decrease the Size of a Plot:\n",
    "    -For Figure level functions-\n",
    "        -use height parameter\n",
    "    -For Axis level functions-\n",
    "        -use plt.figure(figsize=())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "35f6607f-23a4-4a2a-b2e6-50782927a132",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Advantages of seaborn\n",
    "\n",
    "-simple\n",
    "-reduces line of code \n",
    "-provide layer of abstraction\n",
    "\n",
    "# Disadvantages of Seaborn\n",
    "\n",
    "-It does support for all the plots e.g., pie chart can not be plotted using seaborn\n"
   ]
  }
